Subject: [PATCH] Add Architectural Decision Record (ADR) generation to
 Brownfield
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Addresses the SOC 2 / ISO 27001 audit trail gap: regulated
industries require a log of *why* infrastructure was built or
changed the way it was, not just the resulting Terraform.

Follows the 5-step brownfield-remediation ADR structure supplied:
baseline context, risk/vulnerability delta, import/reconstruction
strategy, refactoring decisions, and drift reconciliation
governance.

- lib/agents/brownfield/adr.ts: new generateADR() function. Built
  deterministically from the already-validated Scanner/Auditor/
  Planner output (real resource names, real finding counts, real
  phase details, real cost figures) rather than free-form LLM
  narrative — a hallucinated resource ID or wrong compliance score
  in a document meant to support an audit would be worse than no
  ADR at all.
- app/api/brownfield/analyze/route.ts: generates the ADR right
  after the scan is saved (so it has a real scan ID to anchor
  the ADR ID to: ADR-<first 8 chars of scan id>), then attaches
  it via an update into the existing migration_plan JSONB column
  — no schema change needed. Included in the SSE 'complete'
  payload too.
- components/brownfield/BrownfieldDetailClient.tsx: new 'Audit
  trail (ADR)' step in the wizard sidebar (between Terraform
  output and Review & export), with a lightweight custom markdown
  renderer scoped to the specific template format (headers,
  bullets, bold/italic) rather than adding a general-purpose
  markdown dependency for one controlled document type. Also
  added a 4th 'Download ADR' button on the Review & Export step,
  shown only when an ADR exists (older migrations predating this
  feature won't have one, and the UI says so rather than showing
  a blank/broken state).

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds (24/24 pages),
no new lint errors (2 pre-existing no-html-link-for-pages issues
in the touched file confirmed via diff — unrelated, 0 matches in
this change's diff).
